<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-04-08T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-04-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="311" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d311">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/562: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-04-08T13:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">April 8,
                                        1927—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received April 8—8:55
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>381. Following from American consul at Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“April 7, 5 p.m. Forty-four Americans left on <hi rend="italic">J. Wo</hi> last night and twelve on <hi rend="italic">Po
                                        Yang;</hi> there now remain seventy-six men, six women and
                                    five children. Additional contingents leaving in a day or
                                    two.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>